caption: This was a great spot for a late weekend breakfast.  We has the avocado toast and the anti-burnout bowl with a side of turkey sausage.  The food was excellent. Great place for healthy options downtown. Counter service format with airy space upstairs and downstairs and lots of good window seating. Menu has a decent amount of vegan options. Loved that they had brown rice instead of white. I thought they could add in some vegan substitutes for meat dishes to the menu, but there was enough to choose from. I tried the Thai tofu bowl and would order it again.  On the downside: I was staying to eat inside and yet they served my tea in a single use cup with a plastic lid. I brought it back to switch into a proper cup, but too late to avoid this unnecessary single use waste. I asked about it and was told it’s standard practice when you order large tea here. Little disappointing, so heads up that you might want to request that your tea not be served in single use cup.

I've been to Lyfe Kitchen many times and it's always a hit or miss. However, I can say now that I've had too many bad experiences to continue to pay a high price for mediocre to bad food. Yesterday was the last strike. I gave 2 stars because at least they attempt at being healthy. I had the Quinoa Crunch bowl. Over 2/3 was quinoa! The rest was cucumber chunks, OVERRIPE tomatoes, topped with a very SMALL portion of arugula, dollop of hummus, a brown, overripe slice of avocado the size of a lemon wedge (not worth $11). Their cooks obviously don't care about their craft. Especially, since I had to tell the manager once that I saw the cook texting, then put his phone down, and started rolling my breakfast burrito DIRTY bare hands. He had someone else remake it. I should have been done with Lyfe then!

These in the picture that I took of my plate are clearly not chicken tenders!!!!  Also, she never told me that the order I made was child's meal. Perto da Av Michigan - 2 quadras.
The staff is incredibly friendly, and the food is vibrantly colored with a great palate of flavors! Very clean restaurant as well!!
